trans-unit.source: The event is raised when an issued token is received from the security token service (STS) during sign-in using WS-Federation.
trans-unit.target: Hendelsen oppstår når et utstedt token er mottatt fra sikkerhetstokentjenesten (STS) under pålogging ved hjelp av WS-sammenslåingen.

trans-unit.source: It is raised before the token is validated.
You can access the issued token through the <xref:System.IdentityModel.Services.SecurityTokenReceivedEventArgs.SecurityToken%2A> property and modify its properties or replace it.
trans-unit.target: Du har tilgang til det utstedte tokenet via den <xref:System.IdentityModel.Services.SecurityTokenReceivedEventArgs.SecurityToken%2A>egenskapen og endre egenskapene eller erstatte den.</xref:System.IdentityModel.Services.SecurityTokenReceivedEventArgs.SecurityToken%2A>

trans-unit.source: You can cancel sign-in processing by setting the <xref:System.ComponentModel.CancelEventArgs.Cancel%2A> property.
trans-unit.target: Du kan avbryte behandling pålogging ved å angi den <xref:System.ComponentModel.CancelEventArgs.Cancel%2A>egenskapen.</xref:System.ComponentModel.CancelEventArgs.Cancel%2A>

trans-unit.source: Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.IdentityModel.Services.SecurityTokenReceivedEventArgs"></xref> class by using the specified security token.
trans-unit.target: Initialiserer en ny forekomst av den <xref href="System.IdentityModel.Services.SecurityTokenReceivedEventArgs"> </xref> klassen ved hjelp av den angitte sikkerhetskode.

trans-unit.source: In the new instance, the <xref:System.IdentityModel.Services.SecurityTokenReceivedEventArgs.SecurityToken%2A> property is set to the token specified by the `securityToken` parameter and the <xref:System.IdentityModel.Services.SecurityTokenReceivedEventArgs.SignInContext%2A> property is set to `null`.
trans-unit.target: I ny forekomst av <xref:System.IdentityModel.Services.SecurityTokenReceivedEventArgs.SecurityToken%2A>er satt til tokenet angitt av den `securityToken` parameteren og <xref:System.IdentityModel.Services.SecurityTokenReceivedEventArgs.SignInContext%2A>er satt til `null`.</xref:System.IdentityModel.Services.SecurityTokenReceivedEventArgs.SignInContext%2A> </xref:System.IdentityModel.Services.SecurityTokenReceivedEventArgs.SecurityToken%2A>

trans-unit.source: Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.IdentityModel.Services.SecurityTokenReceivedEventArgs"></xref> class by using the specified security token and sign-in context.
trans-unit.target: Initialiserer en ny forekomst av den <xref href="System.IdentityModel.Services.SecurityTokenReceivedEventArgs"> </xref> klassen ved hjelp av angitte sikkerhetskode og pålogging kontekst.

trans-unit.source: In the new instance, the <xref:System.IdentityModel.Services.SecurityTokenReceivedEventArgs.SecurityToken%2A> property is set to the token specified by the `securityToken` parameter and the <xref:System.IdentityModel.Services.SecurityTokenReceivedEventArgs.SignInContext%2A> property is set to the value of the `signInContext` property.
trans-unit.target: I ny forekomst av <xref:System.IdentityModel.Services.SecurityTokenReceivedEventArgs.SecurityToken%2A>er satt til tokenet angitt av den `securityToken` parameteren og <xref:System.IdentityModel.Services.SecurityTokenReceivedEventArgs.SignInContext%2A>egenskapen er satt til verdien for den `signInContext` egenskapen.</xref:System.IdentityModel.Services.SecurityTokenReceivedEventArgs.SignInContext%2A> </xref:System.IdentityModel.Services.SecurityTokenReceivedEventArgs.SecurityToken%2A>

trans-unit.source: The sign-in context specified in the control.
Gets or sets the issued security token.
You can either modify the properties of the issued security token or replace it entirely.
trans-unit.target: Du kan endre egenskapene for utstedte sikkerhetstokenet eller erstatte den helt.

trans-unit.source: Gets the sign-in context specified in the control.
trans-unit.target: Henter den pålogging som ble angitt i kontrollen.
